erFor` / `WaitForCacheSync` return type** | Spec line 107 | Medium — returns `map[string]bool` instead of `map[reflect.Type]bool` |\n| **Informer constructors** (`NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, etc.) | Spec line 149 | Medium — no standalone informer constructors |\n| **Tests for client-go** | Implicit | High — zero `*_test.go` files under `client-go/` |\n\n---\n\n### 🔄 DIFFERENT APPROACH (Design Deviation)\n\n| Aspect | Spec | Implementation |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Client architecture** | Real REST client + generated fake | In-memory `ObjectStore` pattern only |\n| **Directory structure** | `clientset/versioned/...` | `client-go/clientset/...` (no `versioned/`) |\n| **Scheme registration** | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` |\n| **Fake clientset** | `clientset/versioned/fake/` with `NewSimpleClientset` | `client-go/clientset/fake.go` with `NewFakeClientset()` + store accessors |\n\n---\n\n### Compliance Score\n\n| Category | Score |\n|---|---|\n| **Interface signatures** | 6/12 (50%) |\n| **Struct/constructor coverage** | 1/5 (20%) |\n| **File structure** | 5/20 (25%) |\n| **CRUD completeness** | 8/10 (80%) |\n| **Test coverage** | 0/1 (0%) — no client-go tests |\n| **Build/compilation** | 1/1 (100%) |\n| **API group/resource correctness** | 3/3 (100%) |\n\n**Overall: ~40% spec compliance**\n\nThe implementation is a **simplified custom client** using an in-memory `ObjectStore` pattern rather than a standard `k8s.io/code-generator` output. Core CRUD operations work correctly, but the spec describes a full generated client with real REST support, discovery, scheme registration, informers with constructors, fake test doubles, and expansion hooks — most of which are absent.","time":{"start":1775833988811,"end":1775833988811}}}
